   <taskbody>
      <context class="- topic/section task/context ">
    Editing role information enables you to manage the system's security by defining permissions to a role  and restricting user access to selective modules or forms in the application.</context>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the module menu, click<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Administration</uicontrol>.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">The<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">ADMINISTRATION</uicontrol>page is displayed.</info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the navigation pane, expand<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">User Management</uicontrol>, and then click<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Security Roles</uicontrol>.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">The<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">SECURITY ROLES</uicontrol>list page is displayed.</info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Select the appropriate role, and then click<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Edit</uicontrol>.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">The<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">SECURITY ROLES</uicontrol> page is displayed.</info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Update the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Role</uicontrol> and <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Description</uicontrol> fields with the appropriate information.</cmd>
            <info product="Exclude_PG_Content" class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">For information on permissions, refer to<xref href="../Permissions/ConfigRolePerms.dita" class="- topic/xref ">Configuring Role Permissions</xref>.</info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Save</uicontrol>.</cmd>
         </step>
      </steps>
      <postreq class="- topic/section task/postreq ">If the role name is modified, ensure that the associated workflows' stakeholders are updated at every stage.<ph class="- topic/ph ">For information on updating a workflow, refer to <xref href="../../Configuration_Toolkit/Workflow_Management/EditWF.dita"
